## Vercel Web Analytics Installation Complete

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for the Next.js App Router project.

### Changes Made

**1. Installed Package**
- Added `@vercel/analytics` version 2.0.1 to dependencies
- Updated using pnpm (the project's package manager)

**2. Modified Files**
- `app/layout.tsx`: Added Analytics component import and integration
  - Imported `Analytics` from `@vercel/analytics/next`
  - Placed `<Analytics />` component in the body element after ThemeProvider
  - Follows Next.js App Router best practices from official Vercel documentation

- `package.json`: Added `@vercel/analytics` dependency
- `pnpm-lock.yaml`: Updated lockfile with new dependency tree

### Implementation Details

The implementation follows the official Vercel Analytics quickstart guide for Next.js App Router:
- Analytics component is placed at the root layout level for site-wide tracking
- Component is positioned within the body element as recommended
- No configuration changes needed - Analytics works out of the box
- Will automatically track page views and create routes at `/_vercel/insights/*` when deployed

### Verification

✅ Build completed successfully with no errors
✅ TypeScript compilation passed
✅ All existing code preserved and working
✅ Analytics component properly imported and integrated

### Next Steps

Once deployed to Vercel:
1. Analytics will automatically start tracking page views
2. Data will be available in the Vercel Analytics dashboard
